    From what i've heard, the racewar servers seem to be more about the PvP aspect of the game, while Rallos essentially just uses PvP as a way of resolving problems, and sometimes creating them.  They're all fun, but cylant is still my highest level charachter, and i'd like to see the PvE aspect of the game before i switch over to Tallon or Vallon.<br>
   Theres also the issue of item loot.  On rallos zek, a pvp death means that the person who caused it is able to loot all of your coin, and one item(does not include items currently in your weapon/range/ammo slots).  On tallon and vallon you're only able to loot coin.  Item loot has it's pros and cons.  It seems to essentially destroy the twinking problem for the most part, which is nice, but you will lose an item once in a while.  How cunning and aware you are will effect how often this happens, though that applies to all servers.<br>
    If you only want to PvP please stay away from the Rallos newbie zones, thats just so uncreative. Go to vallon or tallon and barsh some lighties.  I can however highly recommend one PvP guild on rallos, named the malificus sect.  I'm thinking of joining my troll shaman into the guild to satisfy my need for PvP whenever need be.  While they have killed me on numerous occasions, i respect them highly.<br>
<br>
As fricka said, some specification would help out with our suggestions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utularthemostill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tular the Most Ill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/23/01 7:33:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: list of differences?</span><hr size=1> I want a server where I can fight people when I feel like for the fun of PvP fighting but I don't want to end up losing all my gear to the &quot;naked wizzys that run around pking everyone&quot; where should I look? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/23/01 7:35:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: list of differences?</span><hr size=1> Tallon or Vallon.<br>
Gear loss isn't as big of a problem as people make it out to be on rallos zek, i've only lost maybe two items worth mention in 42 levels(RS boots and legs, both because i was slacking off), but the sporadic killing type thing is definetly a Tallon or Vallon thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulirintz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lirin TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/01 9:23:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: list of differences?</span><hr size=1> cylant,ive heard it the other way.  that there is vary little PKing after 20 on rallos.  i know for a fact that i can go any time i want on tallon and get a good fight going at ANY level.  and i usually dont have to go look.  <br>
<br>
course, this is all hersy, i dont really know what rallos is like at all.  not even at newbie levels. <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/drunkmonkus/CoNForever.jpg"> 
